cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about improving the performance of single-stage object detectors using a cascade approach. The paper focuses on analyzing and addressing the inconsistency issue in single-stage detectors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel Feature Consistency Module, which involves training sequential stages with increasing IoU thresholds, indicating that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a multistage object detector, which involves training sequential stages, indicating that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of robotics, indicating that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
